<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,258,858]" box="[151,636,258,282]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Length. Male: 4.0– 
<quantity box="[368,447,258,282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1mm</quantity>
; female: 
<quantity box="[550,631,258,282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,258,858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Color and structure similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pruthi. A" authorityYear="1930" box="[534,718,294,318]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gurawa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minorcephala">
<emphasis box="[534,551,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[564,718,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">minorcephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by slightly shorter vertex with slightly deeper depressed basal area (Plate II: A–B) and slightly shorter face (Plate II: C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,258,858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,366,391]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer side with dorsal margin abruptly curved ventroposteriorly with hind margin tapered and narrowly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[429,524,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1368,1391]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,182,1345]" captionTargetId="figure-240@6.[188,1398,169,1371]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Gurawa truncata sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Style preapical lobe long, apophysis long and digitate (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1300,402,426]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1368,1391]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,182,1345]" captionTargetId="figure-240@6.[188,1398,169,1371]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Gurawa truncata sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus hinged, with basal part articulated to shaft, shaft relatively straight and slightly tapered to truncate apex in lateral and ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[352,474,474,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1368,1391]" captionTargetBox="[199,1390,182,1345]" captionTargetId="figure-240@6.[188,1398,169,1371]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Gurawa truncata sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; C: style, dorsal view; D: connective, dorsal view; E &amp; F: aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Figs 3E–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,258,858]" box="[199,815,510,535]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,511,535]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" reason="1">Female.</emphasis>
Sternite VII posterior margin as in Plate II: D.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
